# Climate Closet Design System

## Core Design Philosophy
- Weather-responsive interface that shifts color schemes based on current conditions
- Sleek, minimal UI with content-first approach
- Single-view focused screens that maximize information density without overwhelming
- Avoid hidden navigation patterns (hamburger menus, bottom tabs) when possible
- Utilize transparency and depth through subtle layering
- Incorporate metallic accents and reflective surfaces for premium feel

## Color System

### Weather-Responsive Base Palettes
- **Sunny**: Gradient from soft yellow (#FFDE82) to warm orange (#FF9B71)
- **Cloudy**: Soft grays (#D1D5DB) with silver accents (#C0C5CE)
- **Rainy**: Blues and teals (#64B6AC to #5591A9)
- **Snowy**: White (#FFFFFF) with ice blue accents (#E1E5F2)
- **Night**: Deep blues (#0D1B2A) with purple hints (#48466D)

### Metallic Accent Colors
- Silver: Linear gradient (#F7F7F7 to #C0C0C0) with 15% opacity overlay
- Gold: Linear gradient (#F4D03F to #D4AC0D) for special elements
- Gunmetal: Linear gradient (#303841 to #3A4750) for important actions

### Transparency Guidelines
- Content cards: 85-90% opacity with blur effect
- Overlays: 40-60% opacity
- Action buttons: 95% opacity with metallic finish
- Status indicators: 80% opacity

## Typography

- **Primary Font**: SF Pro (iOS) / Roboto (Android) / System default
- **Display Font**: Playfair Display for weather headers
- **Title Size**: 28px (bold)
- **Subtitle Size**: 18px (medium)
- **Body Text**: 16px (regular)
- **Caption**: 14px (light)
- **Line Height**: 1.5x font size for optimal readability

## Component Styling

### Cards & Containers
- Rounded corners (12px radius)
- Subtle shadows (x:0, y:4px, blur:12px, color: rgba(0,0,0,0.08))
- Transparent backgrounds (85-95% opacity) with subtle blur effect
- Inner metallic borders (0.5px) that catch light

### Buttons & Interactive Elements
- Pill-shaped primary actions (24px radius)
- Metallic gradient backgrounds that shift with device tilt
- Avoid traditional button borders in favor of elevation shadows
- Tactile micro-animations on press (subtle scale: 0.98)

### Weather Display
- Large, prominent weather icons (custom, not generic)
- Weather condition determines primary gradient of screen
- Temperature displayed with dynamic typography (size relative to extremes)
- Integrate weather animations as subtle background elements

## Layout Philosophy

### Single-View Focus
- Prioritize vertical scrolling over lateral navigation
- Content should be organized in clear visual hierarchy
- Use collapsible sections instead of multiple screens
- Group related information in proximal cards

### Navigation Alternatives
- Instead of bottom tabs: Use horizontal scrolling category chips
- Instead of hamburger menu: Use visible quick-access floating actions
- Instead of deep navigation: Use expandable panels and modal overlays
- Core functions always visible on main screen

## Animation & Interaction

- Weather transitions: Smooth cross-dissolve between conditions (800ms)
- Content loading: Staggered fade-in (200ms delay between elements)
- Feedback animations: Quick (150ms), subtle scale or color shift
- Physics-based scrolling with slight resistance
- Parallax effects between weather background and content cards

## Current Design Trends to Incorporate

- **Glassmorphism**: Frosted glass effect on cards with weather-appropriate tinting
- **Adaptive Color**: UI elements that react to ambient light and weather conditions
- **Variable Typography**: Font weights that subtly shift based on importance
- **Micro-interactions**: Small, delightful animations that respond to user actions
- **3D Touch Elements**: Depth-aware buttons with pressure sensitivity (where supported)
- **Dark Mode Optimization**: Weather appropriate dark modes for evening use
- **Gesture Navigation**: Intuitive swipe gestures for primary actions

## Accessibility Considerations

- Maintain WCAG AA contrast ratios regardless of weather theme
- Provide alternative non-transparent mode for improved readability
- Ensure touch targets are minimum 44x44pt
- Include haptic feedback for all interactive elements
- Design for one-handed use with important actions in thumb zone
